## Overview

Today’s 3‑hour **Problem‑Ideation Micro‑Hack** warms you up for the real-deal Induction/Welcome‑Week hack.

We want you to frame a problem or identify a gap/need, stress‑test feasibility, identify value/feassibility, and what you might need to fix it (or start fixing it!) The ideal outcome of today is a modest **seed file**— a kernel of an idea to grow into a full hack project.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Timeline at a Glance

| Minute | Activity | Purpose | Materials |
|-----------------|------------------|-----------------|--------------------|
| 0 – 5 | **Welcome & rules of play** | Set energy, clarify “no coding yet.” | Slide deck, room mic |
| 5 – 15 | **Lightning context talks** (2 × 5 min) | Seed minds with domain insights. | Laptop, clicker |
| 15 – 25 | **Solo brainstorm – Crazy 8s** | Diverge rapidly. | A4 sheets, pens, timer |
| 25 – 35 | **Affinity wall** | Cluster ideas into themes. | Wall‑space, coloured sticky notes |
| 35 – 50 | **Dot‑vote & Headline** | Converge on top problems. | Dot stickers, Sharpies |
| 50 – 60 | **Team self‑selection** | Form hack teams. | Lean Problem Canvas prints |
| 60 – 120 | **Lunch deep‑dive** | Fill Canvas sections 1‑3 with mentors. | Food, drinks, mentors roaming |
| 120 – 130 | **Round‑robin stand‑ups** | Share drafts, peer feedback. | Bell/timer |
| 130 – 150 | **Value × Feasibility mapping** | Kill/improve risky ideas. | Flip‑chart 2‑axis grid |
| 150 – 165 | **Success metrics + 1st milestone** | Define “what good looks like.” | Prompt cards |
| 165 – 175 | **Lightning pitches** (1 slide, 1 min) | Sharpen story; commit. | Projector |
| 175 – 180 | **Wrap‑up** | Next steps → full hack. | Seed‑file template |

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Materials Checklist  :clipboard:

| Category | Items | Qty. | Notes |
|------------------------|----------------|----------------|----------------|
| **Stationery** | Sticky‑notes (3 colours) | 3 pads / team | Colours by role (dev/design/biz) |
|  | Dot stickers (voting) | 20 / person | Any colour |
|  | A4 paper | 10 / person | For Crazy 8s |
|  | Sharpies / markers | 2 / person | Dark + colour |
| **Display** | Flip‑chart pads | 2 | For 2‑axis grid |
|  | Blu‑Tack / masking tape | — | Affinity wall |
| **Tech** | Projector & clicker | 1 | Slides + pitches |
|  | Countdown timer/app | 1 | Keep pace |
| **Print‑outs** | Lean Problem Canvas (A3) | 1 / team | Download template |
|  | Seed‑file cheat‑sheet | 1 / team | See below |
| **Catering** | Inclusive lunch | — | Encourage working lunch |
|  | Tea / coffee / water | — | Refill station |

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Seed‑File Template  `seed‑file.md`

``` markdown
# Project Title

**Problem Space**  
(1 – 2 sentences)

**High‑Level Description**  
(What are you planning to build or test?)

**HackMaster Volunteers**  
- Name — skill / role
- Name — skill / role

## Resources Needed
- *Experts required?*
- *Skill‑ups needed?*
- *Other resources?*
```

